{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-fill-in-the-blank-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-101","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"title":"Vežba 101","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Glagol <span class=\"highlighted-text\">jog</span> znači trčanje sporim, stabilnim tempom. Reč <span class=\"highlighted-text\">start</span> može biti praćena glagolom koji se završava na <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-ing</span> (kao <span class=\"highlighted-text\">jogging</span>) ili sa <span class=\"highlighted-text\">to</span> praćenim osnovnim tipom glagola (kao <span class=\"highlighted-text\">to jog</span>). Ovo pokazuje početak radnje.</p>\n<p>Adverbijalni glagoli opisuju kako se izvode radnje. Često se formiraju dodavanjem <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-ly</span> na prilog. Na primer, <span class=\"highlighted-text\">regular</span> je prilog koji znači uobičajeno ili često. Kada dodate <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-ly</span>, postaje <span class=\"highlighted-text\">regularly</span>, adverbijalni glagol koji znači nešto uraditi na uobičajen ili često način.</p>\n<p>Primeri:</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">He has a regular exercise schedule.</span>, ili <span class=\"highlighted-text\">He exercises regularly.</span></p>\n</section>","instructions":"","explanation":null,"challengeType":22,"helpCategory":"English","superBlock":"a2-english-for-developers","block":"learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities","lang":"en-US","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a2-english-for-developers/learn-how-to-discuss-roles-and-responsibilities/task-101"},"fillInTheBlank":{"sentence":"<p>I also don't want to neglect my health, so two months ago I started BLANK BLANK.</p>","blanks":[{"answer":"jogging","feedback":"<p>Ovo je stil <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-ing</span> glagola <span class=\"highlighted-text\">jog</span>, koji se koristi nakon <span class=\"highl